default&#xa0;defaultTo what extent should passengers in isolated communities be expected to reldefaulty on taxis and other demand-responsive transport services?default&#xa0;defaultWhere scheduled services are not available either commercially or the Council is unable to support these services taxis and demand-responsive transport services provide a flexible 
defaultsolution which is likely to be more appropriate for the user if it is door-to-door.   The County Council’s view is that the issue is less likely to be around whether the service is a bus, taxi or 
defaultminibus, it is more likely to be because people will have to
default pay for any alternative to scheduled bus services and also that users will need to pre-book the transport.  
default&#xa0;defaultWhilst there is an argument that these services are not comparable to scheduled bus services the Council is clear that there needs to be options 
defaultfor people to travel where these services are not financially sustainable.
