defaultWhat are the main challenges associdefaultated with funding transport services in isolated commudefaultnities? How can these services defaultbe made more affordable?default&#xa0;defaultThe need for ongoing revenue funding at a time when the County Council has a number of pressures in maintaining a range of services including transport, the Council had to take the decision three years ago to withdraw support for some 19 bus services.  The
defaultse services required considerable subsidy to maintain and in some cases alternatives have been found.  The 
defaultlevel 
defaultof bus fares in parts of the County are an issue and this is largely due to the cost of providing services and the distances travelled.  In add
defaultition this situation has not been improved by the availability of ENCTS as operators do not 
defaultreceive
default full fare reimbursed.  The County Council has in the region of 96,000 residents who have concessionary travel passes and in addition a number of tourists tr
defaultavelling in the County who are eligible for “free” transport.”
default&#xa0;
defaultThe County has an ageing population and given the current policy to enable people remain in their own homes for as long as possible this will continue to add demand for transport services and 
defaultconsequent financial pressure to transport budgets.  
default&#xa0;
defaultServices can be made more affordable through efficient planning and coordination of transport requests to make sure that people living in the same area travel at a similar time.  This should generate a
defaultdditional income and reduce the net cost of transport. 
default&#xa0;
defaultA more affordable and efficient transport network could be developed through further integration of services.  This would require flexibility to allow some types of service to carry the “general publ
defaultic” for example, non-emergency patient transport being linked with social care transport or to improve access to the local GP. 
default&#xa0;
defaultTransport services could be means tested so that only those in receipt of certain benefits receive a subsidised transport servi
defaultce.
